               <p>I am apprentice to Mrs. Randall, who is a <rs id="t17760109-32-viclabel168" type="occupation">haberdasher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760109-32-victim306 t17760109-32-viclabel168"></join> in <placeName id="t17760109-32-crimeloc169">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17760109-32-crimeloc169" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17760109-32-crimeloc169" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760109-32-off165 t17760109-32-crimeloc169"></join>: on the 28th of December, between six and seven o'clock, I heard a noise at the window, I ran out and saw the prisoner drawing some riband through the pin-hole of the window; I brought him into the shop; there were six yards besides that I saw him drawing through the hole thrown down the area: I charged him with taking it, and he confessed it: there was a piece of wire found by the window twisted like a corkscrew.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17760109-32-person308">
                  JOSEPH
                   THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t17760109-32-person308" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760109-32-person308" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760109-32-person308" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a constable: I was sent for to take charge of the prisoner; I searched him, but found nothing upon him; I pressed him to tell what was done with some riband that was taken off an empty block we saw in the window, he said he had thrown it down on the cellar stairs.</p>
               <p>The prisoner in his defence denied the charge.</p>
               <p>
